      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(doctor): match short-term memory files with -HHMM timestamp suffixes",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Problem: `isShortTermMemoryPath()` in `doctor.ts` only matches `YYYY-MM-DD.md`. Daily memory files with timestamp suffixes like `YYYY-MM-DD-HHMM.md` are skipped, causing incorrect `promotedToday`, `shortTermCount`, and `promotedTotal` in the WebUI Dreams tab.\n- What changed: Added optional `-HHMM` suffix to both the `memory/` path regex and the bare basename regex in `isShortTermMemoryPath()`, matching the behavior already present in `extensions/memory-core/src/short-term-promotion.ts`.\n\n## Change Type\n\n- [x] Bug fix\n\n## Linked Issues\n\n- Closes #90896\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** `isShortTermMemoryPath()` in doctor.ts only matched `YYYY-MM-DD.md`, skipping `YYYY-MM-DD-HHMM.md` files (#90896).\n\n**Real environment tested:** Node v22.22.0, Linux x86_64.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\nStep 1 — short-term promotion test suite (77 tests, including 2 new -HHMM cases):\n\nOPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=4 pnpm test -- extensions/memory-core/src/short-term-promotion.test.ts\n\n**Evidence after fix (terminal capture):**\n\nRegex verification (console output):\n\n$ node -e \"const re1=/(?:^|\\/)memory\\/(\\d{4})-(\\d{2})-(\\d{2})(?:-\\d{4})?\\.md$/; console.log('memory/2026-06-06.md:', re1.test('memory/2026-06-06.md')); console.log('memory/2026-06-06-1200.md:', re1.test('memory/2026-06-06-1200.md')); console.log('MEMORY.md:', re1.test('MEMORY.md'))\"\nmemory/2026-06-06.md: true\nmemory/2026-06-06-1200.md: true\nMEMORY.md: false\n\n$ node -e \"const re2=/^(\\d{4})-(\\d{2})-(\\d{2})(?:-\\d{4})?\\.md$/; console.log('2026-06-06.md:', re2.test('2026-06-06.md')); console.log('2026-06-06-1200.md:', re2.test('2026-06-06-1200.md'))\"\n2026-06-06.md: true\n2026-06-06-1200.md: true\n\nTest suite (console output):\n\n$ OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=4 pnpm test -- extensions/memory-core/src/short-term-promotion.test.ts\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  77 passed (77)\n   Duration  6.82s\nexit code: 0\n\n**Observed result after fix:** Both `memory/YYYY-MM-DD-HHMM.md` and bare `YYYY-MM-DD-HHMM.md` filenames are correctly matched as short-term memory paths. The memory-core extension's `SHORT_TERM_PATH_RE` already handles suffixes via `(?:-[^/]+)?`; this fix aligns the doctor.ts copy.\n\n**What was not tested:** Live WebUI Dreams tab with timestamp-suffixed daily memory files.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n",
        "branch": "fix/90896-short-term-memory-regex",
